tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild hypoglycemia and slightly low creatinine, which may reflect low muscle mass. Chloride is mildly elevated, but other electrolytes and renal parameters are within normal limits. HbA1c is at the upper end of normal, suggesting good long-term glycemic control. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected; findings are consistent with age-related changes. Clinical correlation recommended.
